    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Fuel System - Cleaning and Inspection</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="s26512.2">
        <title>Cleaning and Inspection</title>
        <svcproc id="m7" svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect fuel lines for misalignment, chaffing or other signs of damage. Replace fuel
                    lines if necessary.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check poppet valve and spring for signs of misalignment. Inspect
                    <hotlnk document="eges3001_E30013.xml" xrefid="f3001309" appearance="hottext">poppet gasket seal
                    </hotlnk>
                    for signs of uneven seating with the fuel filter housing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check fuel return tube for broken or cracking pieces.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean out any accumulated sediment in the bottom of the secondary fuel filter housing
                    and HFCM housing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Wash all fuel filter components in a suitable solvent and dry with filtered compressed
                    air. See
                    <hotlnk xrefid="safety">"Safety Information</hotlnk>."
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check HFCM fuel heater for open or unusually high resistance if a diagnostic trouble
                    code (DTC) was encountered. Refer to Engine Diagnostics.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
